WorkItem.Description:
The restriction (section 3.5.2 of the spec) limits the expressiveness severely.
Here are a couple of legitimate use cases:

```
interface IObservable<T> {
    bufferWithCount( count: number ): IObservable<T[]>;
    materialize(): IObservable<Notification<T>>;
}
```

In addition, on some of these cases (for example, the "materialize" method), the compiler crashes with stack overflow rather than displaying an error message.
